com.ansca.corona
Interface CoronaActivity.OnActivityResultHandler

Enclosing class:
CoronaActivity
public static interface CoronaActivity.OnActivityResultHandler

Handler that is invoked by the Corona activity when a result has been received from a child activity.

This handler is assigned to the Corona activity via its registerActivityResultHandler() method, which returns a unique request code for you to use when calling startActivityForResult().

Method Detail

onHandleActivityResult

void onHandleActivityResult(CoronaActivity activity,
                            int requestCode,
                            int resultCode,
                            android.content.Intent data)
Called when returning from an activity you've launched via the startActivityForResult() method. This method will yield the returned result of that activity.

Parameters:
activity - The Corona activity that is receiving the result.
requestCode - The integer request code originally supplied to startActivityForResult(). Allows you to identify which child activity that the result is coming from.
resultCode - The integer result code returned by the child activity via its setResult() method.
data - An Intent object which can return result data to the caller. Can be null.
